      <lg xml:id="TolE0133">
<l>atte vaṟṟē yāyiru moḻimē</l>
<l>loṟṟumey keṭuta ṟeṟṟeṉ ṟaṟṟē</l>
<l>yavaṟṟumuṉ varūum valleḻuttu mikumē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It is obvious that the consonant</l>
<l>which precedes <foreign xml:lang="ta">attu</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">vaṟṟu,</foreign> these two words,</l>
<l>will disappear, while that which follows them</l>
<l>will be doubled as plosive.<note place="foot">E.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">kalam + attu + kuṟai &gt; kalattukkuṟai ; av + vaṟṟu + kōṭu &gt; avaṟṟaikkōṭu.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
